    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of ornamental and shade tree, often 30 meters (100 feet) in height, having graceful, drooping branches, many-lobed dark green leaves, and large, distinctive acorns about 5 cm (1.7 inches) long. The ash-gray to light-brown bark, slightly orange-tinted, is fissured in irregular cubes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
